message_1:
Consider the formula $\mathbf{AG}\ \mathbf{p}$ where $\mathbf{p}$ is a proposition letter denoting a property of a system that may or may not hold at any given moment in time. Suppose that we have a temporal model with three states $s_0$, $s_1$, and $s_2$ such that:

- $s_0$ is the initial state;
- $s_0$ has a self-loop labelled with $\neg \mathbf{p}$;
- $s_1$ has a loop to itself labelled with $\neg \mathbf{p}$, and a transition to $s_2$ labelled with $\mathbf{p}$;
- $s_2$ has a loop to itself labelled with $\mathbf{p}$.

What is the truth value of $\mathbf{AG}\ \mathbf{p}$ in this model?
